"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-28-paralympics-use-agitos-logo-not-olympic-rings-21504767\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"With three curved swishes in red, blue and green, theParalympicsymbol certainly looks slick.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 92, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"three curved swishes\", \"from\": 5, \"to\": 25}, {\"ngram\": \"theParalympicsymbol\", \"from\": 50, \"to\": 69}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But there is more to the Agitos logo, which is on display at theParis 2024 games, than three colourful lines, with the design signifying the four core values of the Paralympics: courage, determination, inspiration and equality.\", \"from\": 94, \"to\": 321, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 119, \"end\": 125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_symbols\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Agitos\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_symbols\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_symbols\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"display\", \"from\": 144, \"to\": 151}, {\"ngram\": \"theParis 2024 games\", \"from\": 155, \"to\": 174}, {\"ngram\": \"three colourful lines\", \"from\": 181, \"to\": 202}, {\"ngram\": \"the design\", \"from\": 209, \"to\": 219}, {\"ngram\": \"the four core values\", \"from\": 231, \"to\": 251}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paralympics\", \"from\": 255, \"to\": 270}, {\"ngram\": \"courage\", \"from\": 272, \"to\": 279}, {\"ngram\": \"determination\", \"from\": 281, \"to\": 294}, {\"ngram\": \"inspiration\", \"from\": 296, \"to\": 307}, {\"ngram\": \"equality\", \"from\": 312, \"to\": 320}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Red, blue and green were chosen, as they are the colours most used in flags around the world, and the curve in the line shows 'spirit in movement'.\", \"from\": 323, \"to\": 470, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the colours\", \"from\": 368, \"to\": 379}, {\"ngram\": \"flags\", \"from\": 393, \"to\": 398}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 406, \"to\": 415}, {\"ngram\": \"the curve\", \"from\": 421, \"to\": 430}, {\"ngram\": \"the line\", \"from\": 434, \"to\": 442}, {\"ngram\": \"spirit\", \"from\": 450, \"to\": 456}, {\"ngram\": \"movement\", \"from\": 460, \"to\": 468}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Agitos' itself means 'I move' in Latin.\", \"from\": 472, \"to\": 512, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 473, \"end\": 479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_symbols\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Agitos\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_symbols\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_symbols\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Latin\", \"from\": 506, \"to\": 511}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The name symbolises the motion of the Paralympic athletes - but also the Paralympic movement as a whole and the athletes who travel to compete.\", \"from\": 513, \"to\": 656, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 586, \"end\": 605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Paralympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paralympic movement\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Paralympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Paralympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The name\", \"from\": 513, \"to\": 521}, {\"ngram\": \"the motion\", \"from\": 533, \"to\": 543}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paralympic athletes\", \"from\": 547, \"to\": 570}, {\"ngram\": \"a whole\", \"from\": 609, \"to\": 616}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 621, \"to\": 633}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But why are not theOlympicrings used, as well?\", \"from\": 658, \"to\": 704, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These are the ParalympicGames, after all.\", \"from\": 705, \"to\": 746, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the ParalympicGames\", \"from\": 715, \"to\": 734}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's what you need to know.\", \"from\": 748, \"to\": 777, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With many matching sporting events at the Paralympics, you'd think the logos would match, too.\", \"from\": 779, \"to\": 873, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"many matching sporting events\", \"from\": 784, \"to\": 813}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paralympics\", \"from\": 817, \"to\": 832}, {\"ngram\": \"the logos\", \"from\": 846, \"to\": 855}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For example, both Games see competitions in archery, athletics, canoe sprint, cycling, equestrian, football, judo, powerlifting, rowing, sailing, shooting, volleyball, swimming, table tennis, triathlon, basketball, fencing, rugby and tennis.\", \"from\": 875, \"to\": 1116, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 945, \"end\": 951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canoe_sprint\", \"score\": 0.9999307607083162, \"rank\": 6.924408617536357e-05, \"text\": \"sprint\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canoe_sprint\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canoe_sprint\"}, {\"begin\": 962, \"end\": 972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Para-equestrian\", \"score\": 0.9992965797462929, \"rank\": 0.0007010584155024807, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Para-equestrian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Para-equestrian\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 879, \"to\": 886}, {\"ngram\": \"both Games\", \"from\": 888, \"to\": 898}, {\"ngram\": \"competitions\", \"from\": 903, \"to\": 915}, {\"ngram\": \"archery\", \"from\": 919, \"to\": 926}, {\"ngram\": \"athletics\", \"from\": 928, \"to\": 937}, {\"ngram\": \"cycling\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 960}, {\"ngram\": \"football\", \"from\": 974, \"to\": 982}, {\"ngram\": \"judo\", \"from\": 984, \"to\": 988}, {\"ngram\": \"rowing\", \"from\": 1004, \"to\": 1010}, {\"ngram\": \"sailing\", \"from\": 1012, \"to\": 1019}, {\"ngram\": \"shooting\", \"from\": 1021, \"to\": 1029}, {\"ngram\": \"volleyball\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1041}, {\"ngram\": \"swimming\", \"from\": 1043, \"to\": 1051}, {\"ngram\": \", table tennis\", \"from\": 1051, \"to\": 1065}, {\"ngram\": \"triathlon\", \"from\": 1067, \"to\": 1076}, {\"ngram\": \"basketball\", \"from\": 1078, \"to\": 1088}, {\"ngram\": \"fencing\", \"from\": 1090, \"to\": 1097}, {\"ngram\": \"rugby\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1104}, {\"ngram\": \"tennis\", \"from\": 1109, \"to\": 1115}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As it happens, the logos were quite similar once upon a time, until 2003.\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1191, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the logos\", \"from\": 1133, \"to\": 1142}, {\"ngram\": \"a time\", \"from\": 1172, \"to\": 1178}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The original symbol was based on a Korean tae-geuk decoration, and featured blue, black, red, yellow and green symbols - the same colours used at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1193, \"to\": 1352, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1228, \"end\": 1234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"score\": 0.9985804493266871, \"rank\": 0.001417168796145427, \"text\": \"Korean\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The original symbol\", \"from\": 1193, \"to\": 1212}, {\"ngram\": \"featured blue, black, red, yellow and green symbols\", \"from\": 1260, \"to\": 1311}, {\"ngram\": \"the same colours\", \"from\": 1314, \"to\": 1330}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1339, \"to\": 1351}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was unveiled during Seoul 1988, and was said to signify the reality from which all things and values originate.\", \"from\": 1354, \"to\": 1468, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1377, \"end\": 1387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Paralympics\", \"score\": 0.9999977084647861, \"rank\": 2.291540468589782e-06, \"text\": \"Seoul 1988\", \"type